  <Holidays>
    <!--
    Bouvet Island is an uninhabited Norwegian dependency (population 0) administered directly by
    the Polar Affairs Department of Norway's Ministry of Justice and the Police under the
    Dependency Act of 24 March 1933. The only human presence is seasonal researchers at the
    Nyrøysa station during the summer; there is no permanent population and no local legislature,
    so there are no official public holidays.
    -->
  </Holidays>

